title: Trent Cutler
text:
Trent Andrew Cutler is an Australian former professional <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a> footballer. Cutler played for <a href="Bulldogs%20%28NRL%20team%29">Canterbury-Bankstown</a> in the <a href="National%20Rugby%20League">National Rugby League</a> (NRL) competition on the <a href="Rugby%20league%20positions">wing</a>.
Background.
Cutler was born in <a href="Bankstown%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">Bankstown, New South Wales</a>. He is the son of the former Canterbury player, <a href="Stan%20Cutler">Stan Cutler</a>.
Playing career.
As 2004 <a href="NRL">NRL</a> premiers, <a href="Canterbury-Bankstown%20Bulldogs">Canterbury-Bankstown</a> faced <a href="Super%20League%20IX">Super League IX</a> champions, <a href="Leeds%20Rhinos">Leeds</a> in the <a href="2005%20World%20Club%20Challenge">2005 World Club Challenge</a>. Cutler played on the wing in Canterbury's 32-39 loss. He made his <a href="NRL">NRL</a> debut against the <a href="Cronulla-Sutherland%20Sharks">Cronulla-Sutherland Sharks</a> in round 4 of the <a href="2005%20NRL%20season">2005 NRL season</a>.
After three years with Canterbury, Cutler moved to <a href="Western%20Suburbs%20Magpies">Western Suburbs</a> for the 2008 season. In 2009, he has returned to the Canterbury's <a href="NSW%20Cup">NSW Cup</a> feeder club, the Bankstown City Bulls.
